Sorry I snapped, there... I just get really tired of all the &quot;hulk smash... hulk kill !&quot; storylines here.<br>
<br>
You say the clan names are for fairly pumped-up gangs ? Is this a modern story, or a medieval setting ?<br>
If it's modern, I'd stick with something-or-other-ZOKU, then, to show their similarity to the boso-zoku.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Zoku&quot; means &quot;tribe&quot;, &quot;gang&quot;, and &quot;family&quot;.<br>
<br>
The boso-zoku (literally, joyriding-tribe) are the closest things modern Japan has to the motorcycle gangs of the USA.  Unlike the USA, where bikers are adults on big-engine Harleys and wear black leather, Japanese bosozoku gangs are all teenagers and love the pageantry of it all... riding slow and noisy with too many people riding on an overdecorated 'bike, or standing aggressively in a park, with an unfurled banner, hoping that police or another gang will try to shout them away.<br>
<br>
They often have a puffed-up-sounding motto, like a string of nouns describing what's important to them:  &quot;blood, family, revenge, strength&quot; or something like that, which they write on banners alongside the gang name, or on their jackets (long colorful loose-sleeved red robes) or across the top of their bathroom mirrors.<br>
<br>
If this gang is made up of modern teenagers, please check back with me for more advice about how they dress and act.<br>
<br>
If this gang is made up of modern ADULTS, though, the language and way of dressing are completely different... and so, -zoku might be the wrong word for &quot;gang&quot;.  Adult gangs in Japan fall into 2 categories:  loud slobs and slick mafiosa.  <br>
<br>
The loud slobs slouch around with hair combed straight back, wearing black-and-orange Aloha shirts and dark business trousers.  They talk very rudely, shouting everything, and taking offense at everything.  Basically, they're a fistfight waiting to happen... low-level mafia soldiers and money-collectors.<br>
<br>
The higher-up mafia dons are completely different, acting much more like Al Pacino in &quot;The Godfather&quot;:  respectful, well-dressed businessmen in dark sunglasses and dark-windowed luxury cars.  They rarely raise their voice and tend to speak politely.  Still violent, but with a veneer of civility.  They wouldn't do anything violent THEMSELVES, but would delegate it to one of the aloha-shirt-wearing loud slobs.<br>
<br>
Both of those adult groups tend to have shoulder-tattoos.<br>
If you need more info about them, check back.<br>
---<br>
If this is a medieval story, sorry... I don't know much about the medieval lingo.<br>
---<br>
Another example of -zoku should give you an idea of just how often -zoku is used to describe groups in Japan.  The executives in a company who're considered ineffective bench-warmers are called &quot;mado-zoku&quot;, or &quot;window-tribe&quot;, because they spend their days staring out the window. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=1178.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=1178.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1178.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=1178.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=1178.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1178.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1178.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </t